REASONING: According to the CIA World Factbook's Real GDP per capita (PPP) rankings for 2024, Singapore ranks #1 with $132,600 per capita, followed by Luxembourg at $128,200

The Wikipedia list of countries by nominal GDP per capita shows that Monaco has the highest nominal GDP per capita at $256,581 (2023), followed by Liechtenstein at $207,973, and Luxembourg at $140,941 (2025 estimate)
There is a distinction between nominal GDP per capita and real GDP per capita (PPP). Singapore leads in PPP-adjusted GDP per capita, while Monaco leads in nominal GDP per capita
The CIA World Factbook data shows Singapore at the top for real GDP per capita PPP, which adjusts for cost of living differences and purchasing power
Multiple sources confirm Singapore is among the top countries globally for GDP per capita, though the exact ranking depends on whether nominal or PPP-adjusted figures are used
